      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>When <i>α</i>-glucose is treated with an acid catalyst in the presence of an alcohol, an acetal is formed. Propose a mechanism for this process and give the structure of the stereoisomeric acetal that you would also expect as a product.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBazRXIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--a25bab01eea3faf203da0be29ddf3ded01308c78/OChem_19_EC_027.jpg\" alt=\"The reaction shows the conversion of alpha-glucose to acetal in the presence of hydrogen ions and methanol.\">",
